oc:kn_2ef0f87c a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing any threat detection (port scan, DoS, beaconing)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never reimplement detection logic with different thresholds than the helper functions. Use pcap_utils.py functions directly (detect_port_scan, detect_dos_pattern, detect_beaconing) as they handle edge cases correctly." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The helper functions use calibrated thresholds; custom implementations with different thresholds will likely produce incorrect results." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_4d1f05e9 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When detecting C2 beaconing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "C2 beaconing is detected by IAT coefficient of variation (CV) < 0.5. Low CV indicates regular/robotic traffic. High CV (>1.0) indicates normal bursty/human traffic." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Beaconing malware communicates on regular intervals, producing low variance in inter-arrival times." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_5565cd10 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When classifying traffic as benign vs malicious" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Traffic is benign only if ALL three detections are False: no port scan, no DoS pattern, and no beaconing." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Any single malicious pattern present means traffic is not benign." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_8c5ac280 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing flow analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Only count flows from packets that have BOTH IP layer AND transport layer. Always check 'if IP in pkt' when extracting flow 5-tuples." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Transport-layer packets (TCP/UDP) can exist without IP layer in link-layer captures, leading to AttributeError." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_bc2fb3e8 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When detecting DoS patterns" ;
    oc:directiveContent "DoS detection threshold is max/avg packets-per-minute ratio > 20. Ratios of 5x, 10x, or even 15x are NORMAL traffic variations, NOT DoS." ;
    oc:hasRationale "DoS attacks cause extreme traffic spikes; normal traffic can have significant variance that should not be misclassified." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_cc5ca203 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When detecting port scans" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Robust port scan detection requires ALL THREE signals simultaneously: port entropy > 6.0, SYN-only ratio > 0.7, AND unique ports > 100. If ANY condition is not met, there is NO port scan." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Simple single-threshold detection fails due to legitimate users hitting many ports over time, distributed scans, and half-open scan variations." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e3b778f6 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When computing graph_metrics (indegree/outdegree)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never count total packets instead of unique IPs when computing graph degree metrics. Degree = number of UNIQUE IPs communicated with, NOT packet count." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Counting packets inflates degree to thousands; for a 38-node network, max_indegree should be at most 37." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_e53f5048 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When iterating over any packet list (tcp_packets, udp_packets, or raw packets)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always check for IP layer before accessing IP fields: use 'if IP in pkt' guard. ARP and some link-layer packets lack IP layer, and UDP packets may exist without IP." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Non-IP packets (ARP, link-layer protocols) will raise AttributeError if IP fields are accessed without a guard." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_eb8dc379 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When processing large PCAP files" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For large PCAP files, use PcapReader streaming interface instead of rdpcap() to avoid loading entire capture into memory." ;
    oc:hasRationale "rdpcap loads all packets into memory at once; streaming avoids memory exhaustion on large captures." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

